Checklist

Verbose Gradle logs in terminal
Full stacktraces
Remote “step-through” debugging of the Gradle daemon (optional)
App logs (adb) alongside Gradle output
Commands (bash)

From project root, go into Android folder:

cd android
Run builds with rich logs and stacktraces:

./gradlew assembleDebug --info --stacktrace --console=rich
Install and run on device/emulator:

./gradlew :app:installDebug
adb shell am start -n com.cgbowen.ZenGlow/.MainActivity
Tail app logcat (filter to your app):

adb logcat | grep -i zenglow
Check/stop Gradle daemons:

./gradlew --status
./gradlew --stop
Remote debug Gradle (step-through) [optional]

Run a task with Gradle debug enabled (defaults to JDWP on port 5005 and waits to attach):

./gradlew assembleDebug -Dorg.gradle.debug=true
Customize port/attach behavior (optional flags):

./gradlew assembleDebug -Dorg.gradle.debug=true -Dorg.gradle.debug.port=5006 -Dorg.gradle.debug.server=true -Dorg.gradle.debug.suspend=true
Attach a debugger:

With an IDE (recommended) attach to localhost:5005 (or your chosen port)
Or from terminal with jdb:
jdb -attach 127.0.0.1:5005
Persist logging level (optional)

In gradle.properties add:
org.gradle.logging.level=info
Or: org.gradle.logging.level=debug